<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No... a large portion of this board's posters have problems with anons. That don't make a unanimous community decision.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Decisions were made for the calendar here initially, from the selection of people who seek to form sort of order out of the choas. Agreed it is not a unanimous community decision, but it's enough to change the calendar rules if the postings are unanimous here?<br>
<br>
Heck if people don't read the boards then they certainly don't use the calendar.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This is correct. If you suspect an anon is chain-booking, I can check the IP to verify it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wouldn't this create more work than simply not allowing anon postings? Fimble could you please check next week's PoH bookings? 5 days straight, all anon....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And somehow just because someone posts a raid with a name on it, it somehow makes it real?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It doesn't, but it gives other people some reference, to know when the plane was cleared, what was up etc. I have been asked on several raids to help people out, TL'ing etc. as they got stuck LD from a previous raid.<br>
<br>
What I find odd is the number of anon postings now appearing on the calendar, and no one has posted here to defend them except Fimble.<br>
<br>
I went to PoH last night, a good portion of the first floor was clear, previous raid the day before was anon. I have no way of knowing what time they left or if someone came in before us unscheduled.<br>
<br>
Anon postings benefit the individuals making the raids should they wish anonymity for whatever reason.<br>
<br>
Judging by the postings here it is suggested that named postings would benefit users of the calendar as a whole, I don't see anyone coming to the defense (except Fimble) of otherwise. Even make an anon posting here just to be heard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
